# Security Policy

Thank you for your interest in our project! We take security seriously and want to ensure that any security issues are reported and addressed in a timely manner. Please follow the guidelines below for reporting security issues.

## Supported Versions

Use this section to tell people about which versions of your project are
currently being supported with security updates.

| Version | Supported          |
| ------- | ------------------ |
| 5.1.x   | :white_check_mark: |
| 5.0.x   | :x:                |
| 4.0.x   | :white_check_mark: |
| < 4.0   | :x:                |


## Reporting Security Issues

If you discover a security vulnerability or have a security concern, please follow these steps to report it:

1. **Email Reporting**: Send your report to <jidijam.olk@outlook.com>.
2. **Include Details**: Provide a detailed description of the issue, including steps to reproduce and potential impact.
3. **Maintain Confidentiality**: Do not disclose the vulnerability publicly until a fix is available to prevent exploitation.

## Response and Handling

We follow this process to address security issues:

1. **Acknowledge Receipt**: We will acknowledge receipt of your report within 24 hours.
2. **Issue Assessment**: Our security team will assess the issue and provide a response within 7 days, outlining a plan for resolution.
3. **Fix and Notification**: Once a fix is available, we will release an update or announcement to notify users.

## Additional Resources

- [Security Best Practices](https://example.com/security-best-practices)
- [More Information on Reporting Security Issues](https://example.com/security-reporting)

Thank you for your cooperation and support. We are committed to providing a secure and reliable software experience.
